  "prompt": "Can kids look completely different from their birth parents?",
  "response": "Yes, children can look completely different from their birth parents. While genetics play a significant role in determining physical appearance, the combination of genes inherited from both parents can result in a wide variety of characteristics. Additionally, the expression of certain genes can be influenced by complex genetic interactions, making it possible for a child to inherit traits that are not immediately apparent in their parents but may be present in their extended family lineage. Furthermore, environmental factors and individual development can also contribute to differences in physical appearance.",
